<div class="prose-content max-w-3xl">

  <p>We welcome new patients who live within our practice area. Registration is free and available to everyone who is entitled to NHS care.</p>

  <h2>Before you apply</h2>
  <p>Please check that your home address is within our <a href="/new-patients/practice-area/">practice catchment area</a>. If you're not sure, call us on <a href="tel:{{ site.phone | replace(' ', '') }}">{{ site.phone }}</a> and we'll let you know.</p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6 not-prose">
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-dark">
      <li><strong>Already registered with a Levenmouth cluster practice?</strong> We are unable to accept registrations from patients already registered with another GP practice within the Levenmouth cluster. This is a Health Board agreement across the area.</li>
      <li><strong>Transferring from a practice in England?</strong> We strongly recommend you request a copy of your medical records from your current practice before you move. Transfers from English practices can take several months, and having your own copy ensures continuity of your care.</li>
      <li><strong>Moving within Scotland?</strong> If you move outside our practice area after registering with us, you will need to re-register with a practice in your new area. Please do this within 7 days of moving.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2>How to register</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <strong>Download and complete the registration form</strong><br>
      You can download a registration form from the link below, or pick one up from our reception at Leven Health Centre.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Return the completed form to us</strong><br>
      Drop it in to our reception, or post it to us at Leven Health Centre, Victoria Road, Leven, Fife, KY8 4ET.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>We'll confirm your registration</strong><br>
      Once we've processed your form, we'll be in touch to confirm you're registered. This usually takes a few working days.
    </li>
  </ol>

