  <h2>GP allocation</h2>
  <p>You will not be allocated to a specific GP — all of our GPs are able to see all registered patients. However, if you have a preference for seeing a particular GP, please let our reception team know and they will do their best to accommodate this when booking.</p>

  <h2>Documents in languages other than English</h2>
  <p>If you have medical records or documents from abroad, we require accurate English translations before these can be reviewed by our clinical team. Machine translations (e.g. from Google Translate) are not accepted for clinical use. Please arrange a certified translation if your documents are in another language.</p>

  <h2>What information we need</h2>
  <p>The registration form asks for:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Your full name and date of birth</li>
    <li>Your home address</li>
    <li>Your NHS number (if known)</li>
    <li>Your previous GP practice (so we can request your medical records)</li>
    <li>Consent for us to contact you and share relevant health information with other NHS services involved in your care</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>After registering</h2>
  <p>Once registered, you can:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Book appointments by phone or through Patient Access</li>
    <li>Order repeat prescriptions</li>
    <li>Access your health records online through Patient Access</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We'll automatically request your medical records from your previous GP practice. This can take several weeks, but you can still book appointments while we wait.</p>

  <h2>Need help?</h2>
  <p>If you have any questions about registering, please <a href="/contact/get-in-touch/">contact us</a> or speak to our reception team.</p>

